2C113", "https://bloximages.newyork1.vip.townnews.com/2news.com/content/tncms/assets/v3/editorial/7/26/726aa035-d5cb-5696-be9d-37eef41ee428/692e6b56e9a33.image.jpg?resize=200%2C113", "https://bloximages.newyork1.vip.townnews.com/2news.com/content/tncms/assets/v3/editorial/a/e9/ae959b44-8395-56bb-8381-45b6cb4dd0da/692e60b23dede.image.jpg?resize=200%2C113", "https://bloximages.newyork1.vip.townnews.com/2news.com/content/tncms/assets/v3/editorial/5/a2/5a209258-4b65-563d-bfe6-4a6e31aee7a8/692e895dea317.image.jpg?resize=200%2C113", "https://bloximages.newyork1.vip.townnews.com/2news.com/content/tncms/assets/v3/editorial/2/f7/2f7a0fbb-bedd-5518-8552-4e4bb8a4cebc/692be52fb9bf1.image.jpg?resize=200%2C113", "https://bloximages.newyork1.vip.townnews.com/2news.com/content/tncms/assets/v3/editorial/5/74/5746e617-74d3-5ab4-9c6f-d66fb37cab26/692f17f98e4f0.image.jpg?resize=200%2C113", "https://bloximages.newyork1.vip.townnews.com/2news.com/content/tncms/assets/v3/editorial/4/7b/47b74320-5702-5c79-9c9c-25443ad213f0/692e6145958e6.image.jpg?resize=200%2C113", "https://bloximages.newyork1.vip.townnews.com/2news.com/content/tncms/assets/v3/media/4/ea/4eacb190-b57c-11ee-86f2-f3686f22b091/65a8415f88435.image.png?resize=200%2C65"], "publication-date": "2024-07-31", "text": "\n\nLocal law enforcement is serving up food for a good cause.\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nTwo Local Law Enforcement agencies join forces tonight in support of the annual Tip-A-Cop fundraiser event that benefits the Special Olympics.\n\nThe Washoe County Sheriff's Office and The Reno Police Department alongside local Special Olympic athletes are putting their server skills to the test on Wednesday, July 31 as they volunteer with wait staff to help gather tips and donations while delivering their best quality customer service.\n\nThe event is being held tonight at the South Reno Texas Roadhouse located at 150 Damonte Ranch Parkway from 3 p.m. to 9 p.m.\n\n100 percent of \"any\" tips or donations received will be given to the Special Olympics.\n\nThe Reno Police and Washoe Sheriffs are asking the community to help support the Special Olympics by either dining in or ordering online.\n\nA table will be set up at the front of the restaurant to collect any donations.\n\nTexas Roadhouse will give anyone who donates to the Special Olympics tonight a free app card, as a way of saying thank you for the support.\n\nCall ahead seating is also available by calling (775) 852-6333.\n\nYour browser is out of date and potentially vulnerable to security risks.We recommend switching to one of the following browsers:\n\nGet up-to-the-minute news sent straight to your device.", "title": "Texas Roadhouse Reno Hosts Tip-A-Cop for Special Olympics | Local News | 2news.com", "top-image": "https://bloximages.newyork1.vip.townnews.com/2news.com/content/tncms/assets/v3/media/b/4c/b4c6d1ea-6781-11ec-8cfd-038140679c81/65ae8d6ee8713.image.png?resize=200%2C45", "domain": "www.2news.com", "lang": "en", "author": "2 News Nevada Digital Staff", "description": "WCSO and RPD join forces to support and benefit Special Olympics by serving for tips and donations at the Texas Roadhouse in Reno on Damonte Ranch Parkway Wednesday, July 31.", "keywords": "tip-a-cop, special olympics, texas roadhouse, damonte ranch parkway, waiting staff"}